The '''FIBA Women's World Ranking''' is the [[FIBA]]'s rankings of national women's [[basketball]] teams. FIBA ranks women's national teams in both senior and junior competitions. It also publishes combined rankings for all competitions involving both sexes.
==Calculation== FIBA still uses the competition-based system to determine its women's rankings. As noted above, this system was also used to determine men's rankings prior to 2017. FIBA has announced that it will introduce a game-based ranking procedure similar to that currently used for men's rankings in the indeterminate future.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fiba.basketball/documents/rankingmen/faq |title=FIBA World Ranking Men, presented by Nike ‚Äì Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ) |publisher=FIBA |accessdate=16 October 2017}}</ref>
===Events' weights=== FIBA uses a [[weighted arithmetic mean]] to determine the statistical weight of each of the tournaments. Each event is assigned point weight that is based partly on how competitive the tournament is and partly on which national teams are participating:<ref name="how">[http://www.fiba.com/pages/eng/fc/even/rank/p/openNodeIDs/998/selNodeID/998/howItWork.html FIBA.com: How it works]</ref> {|class="wikitable" |- !Number !!width=550px|Event !! Weight |- | 2 || [[FIBA Women's Basketball World Cup]] || 5 |- | 2 || [[Basketball at the Summer Olympics|Olympic basketball tournaments]] || 5 |- | 4 || [[AfroBasket Women]] || 0.2 |- | 4 || [[FIBA Women's AmeriCup]] || 0.8 |- | 4 || [[FIBA Asia Women's Cup]] || 0.3 |- | 4 || [[EuroBasket Women]] || 1 |- | 4 || [[FIBA Oceania Women's Championship]] || 0.1 |}
===Competition ranking points=== [[File:FIFA World Rankings for Women.png|thumb|300px|Map of FIBA World Ranking for women]] As opposed to [[Association football|football]] tournaments, teams still have to go through a series of consolation and classification rounds even if they've been eliminated from title contention, so that a complete ranking of the teams will be possible.<ref name="how"/> {|class="wikitable" |- !width=200px|Competition rank !! Points |- |align=left| Gold medal (1st) ||align=right|50 |- |align=left| Silver medal (2nd) ||align=right|40 |- |align=left| Bronze medal (3rd) ||align=right|30 |- |align=left| 4th ||align=right|15 |- |align=left| 5th ||align=right|14 |- |align=left| 6th ||align=right|13 |- |align=left| 7th ||align=right|12 |- |align=left| 8th ||align=right|11 |- |align=left| 9th ||align=right|10 |- |align=left| 10th ||align=right|9 |- |align=left| 11th ||align=right|8 |- |align=left| 12th ||align=right|7 |- |align=left| 13th ||align=right|6 |- |align=left| 14th ||align=right|5 |- |align=left| 15th ||align=right|4 |- |align=left| 16th ||align=right|3 |- |align=left| 17th ||align=right|2 |- |align=left| 18th and below ||align=right|1 |}
===Cycle and updates=== {| class="wikitable" style="float:right" !Historical #1 teams |- |<timeline> ImageSize = width:140 height:400 PlotArea = left:40 right:0 bottom:10 top:10 DateFormat = mm/dd/yyyy Period = from:01/01/2000 till:08/17/2017 ScaleMajor = unit:year increment:1 start:2000
TimeAxis = orientation:vertical format:yyyy
Colors = id:USA value:rgb(0, 0, 0.55)
PlotData= bar:Leaders width:25 mark:(line,black) align:left fontsize:S
from:01/01/2000 till:08/17/2017 shift:(20,-8) text:"[[United States women's national basketball team|USA]]" color:USA </timeline> |} The calculations are done after the tournaments stated above in a group of two Olympic cycles (8 years). The oldest tournament outside the 8-year period is discarded and replaced with the newest competition.<ref name="how"/>
This means that in every computation, there are: * Four continental championships * Two [[FIBA Women's Basketball World Cup]]s * Two [[Basketball at the Summer Olympics|Olympic basketball tournaments]]
===Example=== The {{wnbt|United States}}' 1000.0 points were calculated by this method: {|class=wikitable |- !Tournament !! Finish !! Points !! Weight !! Result |- | [[2010 FIBA World Championship for Women]] || 1st || 50 || 5 || '''250''' |- | [[2011 FIBA Americas Championship for Women]] || DNP || 0 || 0.8 || '''0''' |- | [[Basketball at the 2012 Summer Olympics ‚Äì Women's tournament|Basketball at the 2012 Summer Olympics]] || 1st || 50 || 5 || '''250''' |- | [[2013 FIBA Americas Championship for Women]] || DNP || 0 || 0.8 || '''0''' |- | [[2014 FIBA World Championship for Women]] || 1st || 50 || 5 || '''250''' |- | [[2015 FIBA Americas Championship for Women]] || DNP || 0 || 0.8 || '''0''' |- | [[Basketball at the 2016 Summer Olympics ‚Äì Women's tournament|Basketball at the 2016 Summer Olympics]] || 1st || 50 || 5 || '''250''' |- | [[2017 FIBA Women's AmeriCup]] || DNP || 0 || 0.8 || '''0''' |- !colspan=4|Total !! 1000.0 |}
After the conclusion of the 2017 continental championships, the points gained from the 2009 continental championships were replaced with those gained from the 2017 editions.
