{{Infobox book | image = File:Oxford_Dictionary_of_Biology.jpg | caption = Cover of the seventh edition | author = Robert Hine, Elizabeth Martin | name = Oxford Dictionary of Biology | country = United Kingdom | language = English | subject = [[Biology]] | published = 2015 ([[Oxford University Press]]) | media_type = Print ([[hardcover]] and [[paperback]]) | pages = 736<ref name="Amazon">{{cite web|title=A Dictionary of Biology|url=https://www.amazon.com/Dictionary-Biology-Oxford-Quick-Reference/dp/0198714378/ref=sr_1_1?s=books&ie=UTF8&qid=1502426296&sr=1-1&keywords=Oxford+Dictionary+of+Biology|website=Amazon.com|publisher=Oxford University Press|accessdate=11 August 2017|language=English|date=25 August 2015}}</ref> | isbn = 978-0-19-871437-8 | oclc = }} '''''Oxford Dictionary of Biology''''' (often abbreviated to '''ODB''') is a multiple editions dictionary published by the English [[Oxford University Press]]. With more than 5,500 entries,<ref>{{cite web|title=A Dictionary of Biology|url=https://global.oup.com/academic/product/a-dictionary-of-biology-9780198714378?cc=en&lang=en&|website=oup.com|publisher=[[Oxford University Press]]|accessdate=11 August 2017|date=25 August 2015}}</ref><ref name="Amazon" /> it contains comprehensive information in English on topics relating to [[biology]], [[biophysics]], and [[biochemistry]].<ref name="OXF">{{cite web|title=A Dictionary of Biology (7 ed.)|url=http://www.oxfordreference.com/view/10.1093/acref/9780198714378.001.0001/acref-9780198714378|website=Oxford Reference|accessdate=11 August 2017|language=en}}</ref> The first edition was published in 1985 as ''A Concise Dictionary of Biology''.<ref name="A Dictionary of Biology">{{cite book|title=A Dictionary of Biology|date=25 August 2015|publisher=[[Oxford University Press]]|isbn=978-0198714378|page=2|edition=7}}</ref> The seventh edition, ''A Dictionary of Biology'', was published in 2015 and it was edited by Robert Hine and Elizabeth Martin.<ref name="OXF" />
Robert Hine studied at [[Kings College London]] and [[University of Aberdeen]] and since 1984 he has contributed to numerous journals and books.<ref name="OXF" />
==Digital and on-line availability== The sixth and the seventh edition edition of the ''ODB'' are available online for members of subscribed institutions and for subscribed individuals via [http://www.oxfordreference.com/view/10.1093/acref/9780198714378.001.0001/acref-9780198714378 Oxford Reference].
==Editions== The first edition of ''Oxford Dictionary of Biology'' was first published in 1985 and the seventh edition in 2015.<ref name="A Dictionary of Biology" />
