== Criticism == The World's 50 Best Restaurants list has been criticised; writing in ''[[The Guardian]]'' in 2003 [[Matthew Fort]] described the list as "humbug".{{r|1TUKm}} The French food writer and critic {{ill|Fran√ßois-R√©gis Gaudry|fr}} says the ranking lacks reliability,{{r|rtSPM}} while the Spanish chef [[Mart√≠n Berasategui]] spoke of "rigged" ranking, manipulated by an "important international food company" in order to "cause damage" to the [[Michelin Guide]].{{r|Pa√≠s 2012}} The list has also been criticised as lacking female representation and being overly Eurocentric.{{r|ZCuCX}}
